97void QAbstractItemViewPrivate::init()
98{
99 Q_Q(QAbstractItemView);
100 q->setItemDelegate(new QStyledItemDelegate(q));
101
102 vbar->setRange(min: 0, max: 0);
103 hbar->setRange(min: 0, max: 0);
104
105 QObject::connect(sender: vbar, SIGNAL(actionTriggered(int)),
106 receiver: q, SLOT(verticalScrollbarAction(int)));
107 QObject::connect(sender: hbar, SIGNAL(actionTriggered(int)),
108 receiver: q, SLOT(horizontalScrollbarAction(int)));
109 QObject::connect(sender: vbar, SIGNAL(valueChanged(int)),
110 receiver: q, SLOT(verticalScrollbarValueChanged(int)));
111 QObject::connect(sender: hbar, SIGNAL(valueChanged(int)),
112 receiver: q, SLOT(horizontalScrollbarValueChanged(int)));
113
114 viewport->setBackgroundRole(QPalette::Base);
115
116 q->setAttribute(Qt::WA_InputMethodEnabled);
117
118 verticalScrollMode = static_cast<QAbstractItemView::ScrollMode>(q->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_ScrollMode, opt: nullptr, widget: q, returnData: nullptr));
119 horizontalScrollMode = static_cast<QAbstractItemView::ScrollMode>(q->style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_ScrollMode, opt: nullptr, widget: q, returnData: nullptr));
120}

122void QAbstractItemViewPrivate::setHoverIndex(const QPersistentModelIndex &index)
123{
124 Q_Q(QAbstractItemView);
125 if (hover == index)
126 return;
127
128 if (selectionBehavior != QAbstractItemView::SelectRows) {
129 q->update(index: hover); //update the old one
130 q->update(index); //update the new one
131 } else {
132 QRect oldHoverRect = q->visualRect(index: hover);
133 QRect newHoverRect = q->visualRect(index);
134 viewport->update(QRect(0, newHoverRect.y(), viewport->width(), newHoverRect.height()));
135 viewport->update(QRect(0, oldHoverRect.y(), viewport->width(), oldHoverRect.height()));
136 }
137 hover = index;
138}
139
140void QAbstractItemViewPrivate::checkMouseMove(const QPersistentModelIndex &index)
141{
142 //we take a persistent model index because the model might change by emitting signals
143 Q_Q(QAbstractItemView);
144 setHoverIndex(index);
145 if (viewportEnteredNeeded || enteredIndex != index) {
146 viewportEnteredNeeded = false;
147
148 if (index.isValid()) {
149 emit q->entered(index);
150#if QT_CONFIG(statustip)
151 QString statustip = model->data(index, role: Qt::StatusTipRole).toString();
152 if (parent && (shouldClearStatusTip || !statustip.isEmpty())) {
153 QStatusTipEvent tip(statustip);
154 QCoreApplication::sendEvent(receiver: parent, event: &tip);
155 shouldClearStatusTip = !statustip.isEmpty();
156 }
157#endif
158 } else {
159#if QT_CONFIG(statustip)
160 if (parent && shouldClearStatusTip) {
161 QString emptyString;
162 QStatusTipEvent tip( emptyString );
163 QCoreApplication::sendEvent(receiver: parent, event: &tip);
164 }
165#endif
166 emit q->viewportEntered();
167 }
168 enteredIndex = index;
169 }
170}

174// stores and restores the selection and current item when flicking
175void QAbstractItemViewPrivate::_q_scrollerStateChanged()
176{
177 Q_Q(QAbstractItemView);
178
179 if (QScroller *scroller = QScroller::scroller(target: viewport)) {
180 switch (scroller->state()) {
181 case QScroller::Pressed:
182 // store the current selection in case we start scrolling
183 if (q->selectionModel()) {
184 oldSelection = q->selectionModel()->selection();
185 oldCurrent = q->selectionModel()->currentIndex();
186 }
187 break;
188
189 case QScroller::Dragging:
190 // restore the old selection if we really start scrolling
191 if (q->selectionModel()) {
192 q->selectionModel()->select(selection: oldSelection, command: QItemSelectionModel::ClearAndSelect);
193 // block autoScroll logic while we are already handling scrolling
194 const bool wasAutoScroll = autoScroll;
195 autoScroll = false;
196 q->selectionModel()->setCurrentIndex(index: oldCurrent, command: QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate);
197 autoScroll = wasAutoScroll;
198 }
199 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
200
201 default:
202 oldSelection = QItemSelection();
203 oldCurrent = QModelIndex();
204 break;
205 }
206 }
207}

221/*!
222 \class QAbstractItemView
223
224 \brief The QAbstractItemView class provides the basic functionality for
225 item view classes.
226
227 \ingroup model-view
228 \inmodule QtWidgets
229
230 QAbstractItemView class is the base class for every standard view
231 that uses a QAbstractItemModel. QAbstractItemView is an abstract
232 class and cannot itself be instantiated. It provides a standard
233 interface for interoperating with models through the signals and
234 slots mechanism, enabling subclasses to be kept up-to-date with
235 changes to their models. This class provides standard support for
236 keyboard and mouse navigation, viewport scrolling, item editing,
237 and selections. The keyboard navigation implements this
238 functionality:
239
240 \table
241 \header
242 \li Keys
243 \li Functionality
244 \row
245 \li Arrow keys
246 \li Changes the current item and selects it.
247 \row
248 \li Ctrl+Arrow keys
249 \li Changes the current item but does not select it.
250 \row
251 \li Shift+Arrow keys
252 \li Changes the current item and selects it. The previously
253 selected item(s) is not deselected.
254 \row
255 \li Ctrl+Space
256 \li Toggles selection of the current item.
257 \row
258 \li Tab/Backtab
259 \li Changes the current item to the next/previous item.
260 \row
261 \li Home/End
262 \li Selects the first/last item in the model.
263 \row
264 \li Page up/Page down
265 \li Scrolls the rows shown up/down by the number of
266 visible rows in the view.
267 \row
268 \li Ctrl+A
269 \li Selects all items in the model.
270 \endtable
271
272 Note that the above table assumes that the
273 \l{selectionMode}{selection mode} allows the operations. For
274 instance, you cannot select items if the selection mode is
275 QAbstractItemView::NoSelection.
276
277 The QAbstractItemView class is one of the \l{Model/View Classes}
278 and is part of Qt's \l{Model/View Programming}{model/view framework}.
279
280 The view classes that inherit QAbstractItemView only need
281 to implement their own view-specific functionality, such as
282 drawing items, returning the geometry of items, finding items,
283 etc.
284
285 QAbstractItemView provides common slots such as edit() and
286 setCurrentIndex(). Many protected slots are also provided, including
287 dataChanged(), rowsInserted(), rowsAboutToBeRemoved(), selectionChanged(),
288 and currentChanged().
289
290 The root item is returned by rootIndex(), and the current item by
291 currentIndex(). To make sure that an item is visible use
292 scrollTo().
293
294 Some of QAbstractItemView's functions are concerned with
295 scrolling, for example setHorizontalScrollMode() and
296 setVerticalScrollMode(). To set the range of the scroll bars, you
297 can, for example, reimplement the view's resizeEvent() function:
298
299 \snippet code/src_gui_itemviews_qabstractitemview.cpp 0
300
301 Note that the range is not updated until the widget is shown.
302
303 Several other functions are concerned with selection control; for
304 example setSelectionMode(), and setSelectionBehavior(). This class
305 provides a default selection model to work with
306 (selectionModel()), but this can be replaced by using
307 setSelectionModel() with an instance of QItemSelectionModel.
308
309 For complete control over the display and editing of items you can
310 specify a delegate with setItemDelegate().
311
312 QAbstractItemView provides a lot of protected functions. Some are
313 concerned with editing, for example, edit(), and commitData(),
314 whilst others are keyboard and mouse event handlers.
315
316 \note If you inherit QAbstractItemView and intend to update the contents
317 of the viewport, you should use viewport->update() instead of
318 \l{QWidget::update()}{update()} as all painting operations take place on the
319 viewport.
320
321 \sa {View Classes}, {Model/View Programming}, QAbstractItemModel, {Chart Example}
322*/
323
324/*!
325 \enum QAbstractItemView::SelectionMode
326
327 This enum indicates how the view responds to user selections:
328
329 \value SingleSelection When the user selects an item, any already-selected
330 item becomes unselected. It is possible for the user to deselect the selected
331 item by pressing the Ctrl key when clicking the selected item.
332
333 \value ContiguousSelection When the user selects an item in the usual way,
334 the selection is cleared and the new item selected. However, if the user
335 presses the Shift key while clicking on an item, all items between the
336 current item and the clicked item are selected or unselected, depending on
337 the state of the clicked item.
338
339 \value ExtendedSelection When the user selects an item in the usual way,
340 the selection is cleared and the new item selected. However, if the user
341 presses the Ctrl key when clicking on an item, the clicked item gets
342 toggled and all other items are left untouched. If the user presses the
343 Shift key while clicking on an item, all items between the current item
344 and the clicked item are selected or unselected, depending on the state of
345 the clicked item. Multiple items can be selected by dragging the mouse over
346 them.
347
348 \value MultiSelection When the user selects an item in the usual way, the
349 selection status of that item is toggled and the other items are left
350 alone. Multiple items can be toggled by dragging the mouse over them.
351
352 \value NoSelection Items cannot be selected.
353
354 The most commonly used modes are SingleSelection and ExtendedSelection.
355*/
356
357/*!
358 \enum QAbstractItemView::SelectionBehavior
359
360 \value SelectItems Selecting single items.
361 \value SelectRows Selecting only rows.
362 \value SelectColumns Selecting only columns.
363*/
364
365/*!
366 \enum QAbstractItemView::ScrollHint
367
368 \value EnsureVisible Scroll to ensure that the item is visible.
369 \value PositionAtTop Scroll to position the item at the top of the
370 viewport.
371 \value PositionAtBottom Scroll to position the item at the bottom of the
372 viewport.
373 \value PositionAtCenter Scroll to position the item at the center of the
374 viewport.
375*/
376

378/*!
379 \enum QAbstractItemView::EditTrigger
380
381 This enum describes actions which will initiate item editing.
382
383 \value NoEditTriggers No editing possible.
384 \value CurrentChanged Editing start whenever current item changes.
385 \value DoubleClicked Editing starts when an item is double clicked.
386 \value SelectedClicked Editing starts when clicking on an already selected
387 item.
388 \value EditKeyPressed Editing starts when the platform edit key has been
389 pressed over an item.
390 \value AnyKeyPressed Editing starts when any key is pressed over an item.
391 \value AllEditTriggers Editing starts for all above actions.
392*/
393
394/*!
395 \enum QAbstractItemView::CursorAction
396
397 This enum describes the different ways to navigate between items,
398 \sa moveCursor()
399
400 \value MoveUp Move to the item above the current item.
401 \value MoveDown Move to the item below the current item.
402 \value MoveLeft Move to the item left of the current item.
403 \value MoveRight Move to the item right of the current item.
404 \value MoveHome Move to the top-left corner item.
405 \value MoveEnd Move to the bottom-right corner item.
406 \value MovePageUp Move one page up above the current item.
407 \value MovePageDown Move one page down below the current item.
408 \value MoveNext Move to the item after the current item.
409 \value MovePrevious Move to the item before the current item.
410*/
411
412/*!
413 \enum QAbstractItemView::State
414
415 Describes the different states the view can be in. This is usually
416 only interesting when reimplementing your own view.
417
418 \value NoState The is the default state.
419 \value DraggingState The user is dragging items.
420 \value DragSelectingState The user is selecting items.
421 \value EditingState The user is editing an item in a widget editor.
422 \value ExpandingState The user is opening a branch of items.
423 \value CollapsingState The user is closing a branch of items.
424 \value AnimatingState The item view is performing an animation.
425*/
426
427/*!
428 \since 4.2
429 \enum QAbstractItemView::ScrollMode
430
431 Describes how the scrollbar should behave. When setting the scroll mode
432 to ScrollPerPixel the single step size will adjust automatically unless
433 it was set explicitly using \l{QAbstractSlider::}{setSingleStep()}.
434 The automatic adjustment can be restored by setting the single step size to -1.
435
436 \value ScrollPerItem The view will scroll the contents one item at a time.
437 \value ScrollPerPixel The view will scroll the contents one pixel at a time.
438*/

636/*!
637 Sets the \a model for the view to present.
638
639 This function will create and set a new selection model, replacing any
640 model that was previously set with setSelectionModel(). However, the old
641 selection model will not be deleted as it may be shared between several
642 views. We recommend that you delete the old selection model if it is no
643 longer required. This is done with the following code:
644
645 \snippet code/src_gui_itemviews_qabstractitemview.cpp 2
646
647 If both the old model and the old selection model do not have parents, or
648 if their parents are long-lived objects, it may be preferable to call their
649 deleteLater() functions to explicitly delete them.
650
651 The view \e{does not} take ownership of the model unless it is the model's
652 parent object because the model may be shared between many different views.
653
654 \sa selectionModel(), setSelectionModel()
655*/
656void QAbstractItemView::setModel(QAbstractItemModel *model)
657{
658 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
659 if (model == d->model)
660 return;
661 if (d->model && d->model != QAbstractItemModelPrivate::staticEmptyModel()) {
662 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(destroyed()),
663 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_modelDestroyed()));
664 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(dataChanged(QModelIndex, QModelIndex, QList<int>)), receiver: this,
665 SLOT(dataChanged(QModelIndex, QModelIndex, QList<int>)));
666 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(headerDataChanged(Qt::Orientation,int,int)),
667 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_headerDataChanged()));
668 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
669 receiver: this, SLOT(rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)));
670 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsAboutToBeRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
671 receiver: this, SLOT(rowsAboutToBeRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
672 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
673 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
674 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsMoved(QModelIndex,int,int,QModelIndex,int)),
675 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsMoved(QModelIndex,int,int,QModelIndex,int)));
676 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
677 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)));
678 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(columnsAboutToBeRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
679 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_columnsAboutToBeRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
680 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(columnsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
681 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_columnsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
682 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(columnsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
683 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_columnsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)));
684 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(columnsMoved(QModelIndex,int,int,QModelIndex,int)),
685 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_columnsMoved(QModelIndex,int,int,QModelIndex,int)));
686
687 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(modelReset()), receiver: this, SLOT(reset()));
688 disconnect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(layoutChanged()), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_layoutChanged()));
689 }
690 d->model = (model ? model : QAbstractItemModelPrivate::staticEmptyModel());
691
692 if (d->model != QAbstractItemModelPrivate::staticEmptyModel()) {
693 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(destroyed()),
694 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_modelDestroyed()));
695 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(dataChanged(QModelIndex, QModelIndex, QList<int>)), receiver: this,
696 SLOT(dataChanged(QModelIndex, QModelIndex, QList<int>)));
697 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(headerDataChanged(Qt::Orientation,int,int)),
698 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_headerDataChanged()));
699 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
700 receiver: this, SLOT(rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)));
701 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),
702 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)));

706 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));

708 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_rowsMoved(QModelIndex,int,int,QModelIndex,int)));
709 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(columnsAboutToBeRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
710 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_columnsAboutToBeRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
711 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(columnsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)),
712 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_columnsRemoved(QModelIndex,int,int)));
713 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(columnsInserted(QModelIndex,int,int)),

716 receiver: this, SLOT(_q_columnsMoved(QModelIndex,int,int,QModelIndex,int)));

718 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(modelReset()), receiver: this, SLOT(reset()));
719 connect(sender: d->model, SIGNAL(layoutChanged()), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_layoutChanged()));
720 }

738/*!
739 Sets the current selection model to the given \a selectionModel.
740
741 Note that, if you call setModel() after this function, the given \a selectionModel
742 will be replaced by one created by the view.
743
744 \note It is up to the application to delete the old selection model if it is no
745 longer needed; i.e., if it is not being used by other views. This will happen
746 automatically when its parent object is deleted. However, if it does not have a
747 parent, or if the parent is a long-lived object, it may be preferable to call its
748 deleteLater() function to explicitly delete it.
749
750 \sa selectionModel(), setModel(), clearSelection()
751*/
752void QAbstractItemView::setSelectionModel(QItemSelectionModel *selectionModel)
753{
754 // ### if the given model is null, we should use the original selection model
755 Q_ASSERT(selectionModel);
756 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
757
758 if (Q_UNLIKELY(selectionModel->model() != d->model)) {
759 qWarning(msg: "QAbstractItemView::setSelectionModel() failed: "
760 "Trying to set a selection model, which works on "
761 "a different model than the view.");
762 return;
763 }
764
765 QItemSelection oldSelection;
766 QModelIndex oldCurrentIndex;
767
768 if (d->selectionModel) {
769 if (d->selectionModel->model() == selectionModel->model()) {
770 oldSelection = d->selectionModel->selection();
771 oldCurrentIndex = d->selectionModel->currentIndex();
772 }
773
774 disconnect(sender: d->selectionModel, SIGNAL(selectionChanged(QItemSelection,QItemSelection)),
775 receiver: this, SLOT(selectionChanged(QItemSelection,QItemSelection)));
776 disconnect(sender: d->selectionModel, SIGNAL(currentChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)),
777 receiver: this, SLOT(currentChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)));
778 }
779
780 d->selectionModel = selectionModel;
781
782 if (d->selectionModel) {
783 connect(sender: d->selectionModel, SIGNAL(selectionChanged(QItemSelection,QItemSelection)),
784 receiver: this, SLOT(selectionChanged(QItemSelection,QItemSelection)));
785 connect(sender: d->selectionModel, SIGNAL(currentChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)),
786 receiver: this, SLOT(currentChanged(QModelIndex,QModelIndex)));
787
788 selectionChanged(selected: d->selectionModel->selection(), deselected: oldSelection);
789 currentChanged(current: d->selectionModel->currentIndex(), previous: oldCurrentIndex);
790 }
791}

804/*!
805 Sets the item delegate for this view and its model to \a delegate.
806 This is useful if you want complete control over the editing and
807 display of items.
808
809 Any existing delegate will be removed, but not deleted. QAbstractItemView
810 does not take ownership of \a delegate.
811
812 \warning You should not share the same instance of a delegate between views.
813 Doing so can cause incorrect or unintuitive editing behavior since each
814 view connected to a given delegate may receive the \l{QAbstractItemDelegate::}{closeEditor()}
815 signal, and attempt to access, modify or close an editor that has already been closed.
816
817 \sa itemDelegate()
818*/
819void QAbstractItemView::setItemDelegate(QAbstractItemDelegate *delegate)
820{
821 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
822 if (delegate == d->itemDelegate)
823 return;
824
825 if (d->itemDelegate) {
826 if (d->delegateRefCount(delegate: d->itemDelegate) == 1) {
827 disconnect(sender: d->itemDelegate, SIGNAL(closeEditor(QWidget*,QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint)),
828 receiver: this, SLOT(closeEditor(QWidget*,QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint)));
829 disconnect(sender: d->itemDelegate, SIGNAL(commitData(QWidget*)), receiver: this, SLOT(commitData(QWidget*)));
830 disconnect(sender: d->itemDelegate, SIGNAL(sizeHintChanged(QModelIndex)), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_delegateSizeHintChanged(QModelIndex)));
831 }
832 }
833
834 if (delegate) {
835 if (d->delegateRefCount(delegate) == 0) {
836 connect(sender: delegate, SIGNAL(closeEditor(QWidget*,QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint)),
837 receiver: this, SLOT(closeEditor(QWidget*,QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint)));
838 connect(sender: delegate, SIGNAL(commitData(QWidget*)), receiver: this, SLOT(commitData(QWidget*)));
839 connect(sender: delegate, SIGNAL(sizeHintChanged(QModelIndex)), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_delegateSizeHintChanged(QModelIndex)));
840 }
841 }
842 d->itemDelegate = delegate;
843 viewport()->update();
844 d->doDelayedItemsLayout();
845}

854{
855 return d_func()->itemDelegate;

858/*!
859 \reimp
860*/
861QVariant QAbstractItemView::inputMethodQuery(Qt::InputMethodQuery query) const
862{
863 Q_D(const QAbstractItemView);
864 const QModelIndex current = currentIndex();
865 QVariant result;
866 if (current.isValid()) {
867 if (QWidget *currentEditor;
868 d->waitForIMCommit && (currentEditor = d->editorForIndex(index: current).widget)) {
869 // An editor is open but the initial preedit is still ongoing. Delegate
870 // queries to the editor and map coordinates from editor to this view.
871 result = currentEditor->inputMethodQuery(query);
872 if (result.typeId() == QMetaType::QRect) {
873 const QRect editorRect = result.value<QRect>();
874 result = QRect(currentEditor->mapTo(this, editorRect.topLeft()), editorRect.size());
875 }
876 } else if (query == Qt::ImCursorRectangle) {
877 result = visualRect(index: current);
878 }
879 }
880 if (!result.isValid())
881 result = QAbstractScrollArea::inputMethodQuery(query);
882 return result;
883}

885/*!
886 \since 4.2
887
888 Sets the given item \a delegate used by this view and model for the given
889 \a row. All items on \a row will be drawn and managed by \a delegate
890 instead of using the default delegate (i.e., itemDelegate()).
891
892 Any existing row delegate for \a row will be removed, but not
893 deleted. QAbstractItemView does not take ownership of \a delegate.
894
895 \note If a delegate has been assigned to both a row and a column, the row
896 delegate (i.e., this delegate) will take precedence and manage the
897 intersecting cell index.
898
899 \warning You should not share the same instance of a delegate between views.
900 Doing so can cause incorrect or unintuitive editing behavior since each
901 view connected to a given delegate may receive the \l{QAbstractItemDelegate::}{closeEditor()}
902 signal, and attempt to access, modify or close an editor that has already been closed.
903
904 \sa itemDelegateForRow(), setItemDelegateForColumn(), itemDelegate()
905*/
906void QAbstractItemView::setItemDelegateForRow(int row, QAbstractItemDelegate *delegate)
907{
908 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
909 if (QAbstractItemDelegate *rowDelegate = d->rowDelegates.value(key: row, defaultValue: nullptr)) {
910 if (d->delegateRefCount(delegate: rowDelegate) == 1) {
911 disconnect(sender: rowDelegate, SIGNAL(closeEditor(QWidget*,QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint)),
912 receiver: this, SLOT(closeEditor(QWidget*,QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint)));
913 disconnect(sender: rowDelegate, SIGNAL(commitData(QWidget*)), receiver: this, SLOT(commitData(QWidget*)));
914 disconnect(sender: rowDelegate, SIGNAL(sizeHintChanged(QModelIndex)), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_delegateSizeHintChanged(QModelIndex)));
915 }
916 d->rowDelegates.remove(key: row);
917 }
918 if (delegate) {
919 if (d->delegateRefCount(delegate) == 0) {
920 connect(sender: delegate, SIGNAL(closeEditor(QWidget*,QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint)),
921 receiver: this, SLOT(closeEditor(QWidget*,QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint)));
922 connect(sender: delegate, SIGNAL(commitData(QWidget*)), receiver: this, SLOT(commitData(QWidget*)));
923 connect(sender: delegate, SIGNAL(sizeHintChanged(QModelIndex)), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_delegateSizeHintChanged(QModelIndex)));
924 }
925 d->rowDelegates.insert(key: row, value: delegate);
926 }
927 viewport()->update();
928 d->doDelayedItemsLayout();
929}

1109/*!
1110 Reset the internal state of the view.
1111
1112 \warning This function will reset open editors, scroll bar positions,
1113 selections, etc. Existing changes will not be committed. If you would like
1114 to save your changes when resetting the view, you can reimplement this
1115 function, commit your changes, and then call the superclass'
1116 implementation.
1117*/
1118void QAbstractItemView::reset()
1119{
1120 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1121 d->delayedReset.stop(); //make sure we stop the timer
1122 foreach (const QEditorInfo &info, d->indexEditorHash) {
1123 if (info.widget)
1124 d->releaseEditor(editor: info.widget.data(), index: d->indexForEditor(editor: info.widget.data()));
1125 }
1126 d->editorIndexHash.clear();
1127 d->indexEditorHash.clear();
1128 d->persistent.clear();
1129 d->currentIndexSet = false;
1130 setState(NoState);
1131 setRootIndex(QModelIndex());
1132 if (d->selectionModel)
1133 d->selectionModel->reset();
1134#if QT_CONFIG(accessibility)
1135 if (QAccessible::isActive()) {
1136 QAccessibleTableModelChangeEvent accessibleEvent(this, QAccessibleTableModelChangeEvent::ModelReset);
1137 QAccessible::updateAccessibility(event: &accessibleEvent);
1138 }
1139#endif
1140 d->updateGeometry();
1141}

1171/*!
1172 Selects all items in the view.
1173 This function will use the selection behavior
1174 set on the view when selecting.
1175
1176 \sa setSelection(), selectedIndexes(), clearSelection()
1177*/
1178void QAbstractItemView::selectAll()
1179{
1180 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1181 const SelectionMode mode = d->selectionMode;
1182 switch (mode) {
1183 case MultiSelection:
1184 case ExtendedSelection:
1185 d->selectAll(command: QItemSelectionModel::ClearAndSelect
1186 | d->selectionBehaviorFlags());
1187 break;
1188 case NoSelection:
1189 case ContiguousSelection:
1190 if (d->model->hasChildren(parent: d->root))
1191 d->selectAll(command: selectionCommand(index: d->model->index(row: 0, column: 0, parent: d->root)));
1192 break;
1193 case SingleSelection:
1194 break;
1195 }
1196}

1272 Scrolling can be done either per pixel or per item. Its default value

1275
1276void QAbstractItemView::setVerticalScrollMode(ScrollMode mode)
1277{
1278 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1279 d->verticalScrollModeSet = true;
1280 if (mode == d->verticalScrollMode)
1281 return;
1282 QModelIndex topLeft = indexAt(point: QPoint(0, 0));

1285 verticalScrollBar()->d_func()->itemviewChangeSingleStep(step: 1); // setSingleStep(-1) => step with 1
1286 else
1287 verticalScrollBar()->setSingleStep(-1); // Ensure that the view can update single step
1288 updateGeometries(); // update the scroll bars
1289 scrollTo(index: topLeft, hint: QAbstractItemView::PositionAtTop);
1290}

1301 setVerticalScrollMode(sm);

1346 \brief the view's drag and drop behavior
1347
1348 If its value is \c true, the selected data will overwrite the
1349 existing item data when dropped, while moving the data will clear
1350 the item. If its value is \c false, the selected data will be
1351 inserted as a new item when the data is dropped. When the data is
1352 moved, the item is removed as well.
1353
1354 The default value is \c false, as in the QListView and QTreeView
1355 subclasses. In the QTableView subclass, on the other hand, the
1356 property has been set to \c true.
1357
1358 Note: This is not intended to prevent overwriting of items.
1359 The model's implementation of flags() should do that by not
1360 returning Qt::ItemIsDropEnabled.
1361
1362 \sa dragDropMode
1363*/
1364void QAbstractItemView::setDragDropOverwriteMode(bool overwrite)
1365{

1367 d->overwrite = overwrite;
1368}

1488/*!
1489 \since 4.2
1490 \enum QAbstractItemView::DragDropMode
1491
1492 Describes the various drag and drop events the view can act upon.
1493 By default the view does not support dragging or dropping (\c
1494 NoDragDrop).
1495
1496 \value NoDragDrop Does not support dragging or dropping.
1497 \value DragOnly The view supports dragging of its own items
1498 \value DropOnly The view accepts drops
1499 \value DragDrop The view supports both dragging and dropping
1500 \value InternalMove The view accepts move (\b{not copy}) operations only
1501 from itself.
1502
1503 Note that the model used needs to provide support for drag and drop operations.
1504
1505 \sa setDragDropMode(), {Using drag and drop with item views}
1506*/
1507
1508/*!
1509 \property QAbstractItemView::dragDropMode
1510 \brief the drag and drop event the view will act upon
1511
1512 \since 4.2
1513 \sa showDropIndicator, dragDropOverwriteMode
1514*/
1515void QAbstractItemView::setDragDropMode(DragDropMode behavior)
1516{
1517 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1518 d->dragDropMode = behavior;
1519 setDragEnabled(behavior == DragOnly || behavior == DragDrop || behavior == InternalMove);
1520 setAcceptDrops(behavior == DropOnly || behavior == DragDrop || behavior == InternalMove);
1521}
1522
1523QAbstractItemView::DragDropMode QAbstractItemView::dragDropMode() const
1524{
1525 Q_D(const QAbstractItemView);
1526 DragDropMode setBehavior = d->dragDropMode;
1527 if (!dragEnabled() && !acceptDrops())
1528 return NoDragDrop;
1529
1530 if (dragEnabled() && !acceptDrops())
1531 return DragOnly;
1532
1533 if (!dragEnabled() && acceptDrops())
1534 return DropOnly;
1535
1536 if (dragEnabled() && acceptDrops()) {
1537 if (setBehavior == InternalMove)
1538 return setBehavior;
1539 else
1540 return DragDrop;
1541 }
1542
1543 return NoDragDrop;
1544}

1649
1650/*!
1651 \reimp
1652*/
1653bool QAbstractItemView::event(QEvent *event)
1654{
1655 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1656 switch (event->type()) {
1657 case QEvent::Paint:
1658 //we call this here because the scrollbars' visibility might be altered
1659 //so this can't be done in the paintEvent method
1660 d->executePostedLayout(); //make sure we set the layout properly
1661 break;
1662 case QEvent::Show:
1663 d->executePostedLayout(); //make sure we set the layout properly
1664 if (d->shouldScrollToCurrentOnShow) {
1665 d->shouldScrollToCurrentOnShow = false;
1666 const QModelIndex current = currentIndex();
1667 if (current.isValid() && (d->state == QAbstractItemView::EditingState || d->autoScroll))
1668 scrollTo(index: current);
1669 }
1670 break;
1671 case QEvent::LocaleChange:
1672 viewport()->update();
1673 break;
1674 case QEvent::LayoutDirectionChange:
1675 case QEvent::ApplicationLayoutDirectionChange:
1676 updateGeometries();
1677 break;
1678 case QEvent::StyleChange:
1679 doItemsLayout();
1680 if (!d->verticalScrollModeSet)
1681 resetVerticalScrollMode();
1682 if (!d->horizontalScrollModeSet)
1683 resetHorizontalScrollMode();
1684 break;
1685 case QEvent::FocusOut:
1686 d->checkPersistentEditorFocus();
1687 break;
1688 case QEvent::FontChange:
1689 d->doDelayedItemsLayout(); // the size of the items will change
1690 break;
1691 default:
1692 break;
1693 }
1694 return QAbstractScrollArea::event(event);
1695}
1696
1697/*!
1698 \fn bool QAbstractItemView::viewportEvent(QEvent *event)
1699
1700 This function is used to handle tool tips, and What's
1701 This? mode, if the given \a event is a QEvent::ToolTip,or a
1702 QEvent::WhatsThis. It passes all other
1703 events on to its base class viewportEvent() handler.
1704
1705 Returns \c true if \a event has been recognized and processed; otherwise,
1706 returns \c false.
1707*/
1708bool QAbstractItemView::viewportEvent(QEvent *event)
1709{
1710 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1711 switch (event->type()) {
1712 case QEvent::Paint:
1713 // Similar to pre-painting in QAbstractItemView::event to update scrollbar
1714 // visibility, make sure that all pending layout requests have been executed
1715 // so that the view's data structures are up-to-date before rendering.
1716 d->executePostedLayout();
1717 break;
1718 case QEvent::HoverMove:
1719 case QEvent::HoverEnter:
1720 d->setHoverIndex(indexAt(point: static_cast<QHoverEvent*>(event)->position().toPoint()));
1721 break;
1722 case QEvent::HoverLeave:
1723 d->setHoverIndex(QModelIndex());
1724 break;
1725 case QEvent::Enter:
1726 d->viewportEnteredNeeded = true;
1727 break;
1728 case QEvent::Leave:
1729 d->setHoverIndex(QModelIndex()); // If we've left, no hover should be needed anymore
1730 #if QT_CONFIG(statustip)
1731 if (d->shouldClearStatusTip && d->parent) {
1732 QString empty;
1733 QStatusTipEvent tip(empty);
1734 QCoreApplication::sendEvent(receiver: d->parent, event: &tip);
1735 d->shouldClearStatusTip = false;
1736 }
1737 #endif
1738 d->enteredIndex = QModelIndex();
1739 break;
1740 case QEvent::ToolTip:
1741 case QEvent::QueryWhatsThis:
1742 case QEvent::WhatsThis: {
1743 QHelpEvent *he = static_cast<QHelpEvent*>(event);
1744 const QModelIndex index = indexAt(point: he->pos());
1745 QStyleOptionViewItem option;
1746 initViewItemOption(option: &option);
1747 option.rect = visualRect(index);
1748 option.state |= (index == currentIndex() ? QStyle::State_HasFocus : QStyle::State_None);
1749
1750 QAbstractItemDelegate *delegate = itemDelegateForIndex(index);
1751 if (!delegate)
1752 return false;
1753 return delegate->helpEvent(event: he, view: this, option, index);
1754 }
1755 case QEvent::FontChange:
1756 d->doDelayedItemsLayout(); // the size of the items will change
1757 break;
1758 case QEvent::WindowActivate:
1759 case QEvent::WindowDeactivate:
1760 d->viewport->update();
1761 break;
1762 case QEvent::ScrollPrepare:
1763 executeDelayedItemsLayout();
1764#if QT_CONFIG(gestures) && QT_CONFIG(scroller)
1765 connect(sender: QScroller::scroller(target: d->viewport), SIGNAL(stateChanged(QScroller::State)), receiver: this, SLOT(_q_scrollerStateChanged()), Qt::UniqueConnection);
1766#endif
1767 break;
1768
1769 default:
1770 break;
1771 }
1772 return QAbstractScrollArea::viewportEvent(event);
1773}
1774
1775/*!
1776 This function is called with the given \a event when a mouse button is pressed
1777 while the cursor is inside the widget. If a valid item is pressed on it is made
1778 into the current item. This function emits the pressed() signal.
1779*/
1780void QAbstractItemView::mousePressEvent(QMouseEvent *event)
1781{
1782 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1783 d->releaseFromDoubleClick = false;
1784 d->delayedAutoScroll.stop(); //any interaction with the view cancel the auto scrolling
1785 QPoint pos = event->position().toPoint();
1786 QPersistentModelIndex index = indexAt(point: pos);
1787
1788 // this is the mouse press event that closed the last editor (via focus event)
1789 d->pressClosedEditor = d->pressClosedEditorWatcher.isActive() && d->lastEditedIndex == index;
1790
1791 if (!d->selectionModel || (d->state == EditingState && d->hasEditor(index)))
1792 return;
1793
1794 d->pressedAlreadySelected = d->selectionModel->isSelected(index);
1795 d->pressedIndex = index;
1796 d->pressedModifiers = event->modifiers();
1797 QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags command = selectionCommand(index, event);
1798 d->noSelectionOnMousePress = command == QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate || !index.isValid();
1799 QPoint offset = d->offset();
1800 d->draggedPosition = pos + offset;
1801
1802#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
1803 // update the pressed position when drag was enable
1804 if (d->dragEnabled)
1805 d->pressedPosition = d->draggedPosition;
1806#endif
1807
1808 if (!(command & QItemSelectionModel::Current)) {
1809 d->pressedPosition = pos + offset;
1810 d->currentSelectionStartIndex = index;
1811 }
1812 else if (!d->currentSelectionStartIndex.isValid())
1813 d->currentSelectionStartIndex = currentIndex();
1814
1815 if (edit(index, trigger: NoEditTriggers, event))
1816 return;
1817
1818 if (index.isValid() && d->isIndexEnabled(index)) {
1819 // we disable scrollTo for mouse press so the item doesn't change position
1820 // when the user is interacting with it (ie. clicking on it)
1821 bool autoScroll = d->autoScroll;
1822 d->autoScroll = false;
1823 d->selectionModel->setCurrentIndex(index, command: QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate);
1824 d->autoScroll = autoScroll;
1825 if (command.testFlag(flag: QItemSelectionModel::Toggle)) {
1826 command &= ~QItemSelectionModel::Toggle;
1827 d->ctrlDragSelectionFlag = d->selectionModel->isSelected(index) ? QItemSelectionModel::Deselect : QItemSelectionModel::Select;
1828 command |= d->ctrlDragSelectionFlag;
1829 }
1830
1831 if (!(command & QItemSelectionModel::Current)) {
1832 setSelection(rect: QRect(pos, QSize(1, 1)), command);
1833 } else {
1834 QRect rect(visualRect(index: d->currentSelectionStartIndex).center(), pos);
1835 setSelection(rect, command);
1836 }
1837
1838 // signal handlers may change the model
1839 emit pressed(index);
1840 if (d->autoScroll) {
1841 //we delay the autoscrolling to filter out double click event
1842 //100 is to be sure that there won't be a double-click misinterpreted as a 2 single clicks
1843 d->delayedAutoScroll.start(msec: QApplication::doubleClickInterval()+100, obj: this);
1844 }
1845
1846 } else {
1847 // Forces a finalize() even if mouse is pressed, but not on a item
1848 d->selectionModel->select(index: QModelIndex(), command: QItemSelectionModel::Select);
1849 }
1850}
1851
1852/*!
1853 This function is called with the given \a event when a mouse move event is
1854 sent to the widget. If a selection is in progress and new items are moved
1855 over the selection is extended; if a drag is in progress it is continued.
1856*/
1857void QAbstractItemView::mouseMoveEvent(QMouseEvent *event)
1858{
1859 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1860 QPoint topLeft;
1861 QPoint bottomRight = event->position().toPoint();
1862
1863 d->draggedPosition = bottomRight + d->offset();
1864
1865 if (state() == ExpandingState || state() == CollapsingState)
1866 return;
1867
1868#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
1869 if (state() == DraggingState) {
1870 topLeft = d->pressedPosition - d->offset();
1871 if ((topLeft - bottomRight).manhattanLength() > QApplication::startDragDistance()) {
1872 d->pressedIndex = QModelIndex();
1873 startDrag(supportedActions: d->model->supportedDragActions());
1874 setState(NoState); // the startDrag will return when the dnd operation is done
1875 stopAutoScroll();
1876 }
1877 return;
1878 }
1879#endif // QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
1880
1881 QPersistentModelIndex index = indexAt(point: bottomRight);
1882 QModelIndex buddy = d->model->buddy(index: d->pressedIndex);
1883 if ((state() == EditingState && d->hasEditor(index: buddy))
1884 || edit(index, trigger: NoEditTriggers, event))
1885 return;
1886
1887 if (d->selectionMode != SingleSelection)
1888 topLeft = d->pressedPosition - d->offset();
1889 else
1890 topLeft = bottomRight;
1891
1892 d->checkMouseMove(index);
1893
1894#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
1895 if (d->pressedIndex.isValid()
1896 && d->dragEnabled
1897 && (state() != DragSelectingState)
1898 && (event->buttons() != Qt::NoButton)
1899 && !d->selectedDraggableIndexes().isEmpty()) {
1900 setState(DraggingState);
1901 return;
1902 }
1903#endif
1904
1905 if ((event->buttons() & Qt::LeftButton) && d->selectionAllowed(index) && d->selectionModel) {
1906 setState(DragSelectingState);
1907 QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags command = selectionCommand(index, event);
1908 if (d->ctrlDragSelectionFlag != QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate && command.testFlag(flag: QItemSelectionModel::Toggle)) {
1909 command &= ~QItemSelectionModel::Toggle;
1910 command |= d->ctrlDragSelectionFlag;
1911 }
1912
1913 // Do the normalize ourselves, since QRect::normalized() is flawed
1914 QRect selectionRect = QRect(topLeft, bottomRight);
1915 setSelection(rect: selectionRect, command);
1916
1917 // set at the end because it might scroll the view
1918 if (index.isValid() && (index != d->selectionModel->currentIndex()) && d->isIndexEnabled(index))
1919 d->selectionModel->setCurrentIndex(index, command: QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate);
1920 else if (d->shouldAutoScroll(pos: event->pos()) && !d->autoScrollTimer.isActive())
1921 startAutoScroll();
1922 }
1923}
1924
1925/*!
1926 This function is called with the given \a event when a mouse button is released,
1927 after a mouse press event on the widget. If a user presses the mouse inside your
1928 widget and then drags the mouse to another location before releasing the mouse button,
1929 your widget receives the release event. The function will emit the clicked() signal if an
1930 item was being pressed.
1931*/
1932void QAbstractItemView::mouseReleaseEvent(QMouseEvent *event)
1933{
1934 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1935 const bool releaseFromDoubleClick = d->releaseFromDoubleClick;
1936 d->releaseFromDoubleClick = false;
1937
1938 QPoint pos = event->position().toPoint();
1939 QPersistentModelIndex index = indexAt(point: pos);
1940
1941 if (state() == EditingState) {
1942 if (d->isIndexValid(index)
1943 && d->isIndexEnabled(index)
1944 && d->sendDelegateEvent(index, event))
1945 update(index);
1946 return;
1947 }
1948
1949 bool click = (index == d->pressedIndex && index.isValid() && !releaseFromDoubleClick);
1950 bool selectedClicked = click && d->pressedAlreadySelected
1951 && (event->button() == Qt::LeftButton)
1952 && (event->modifiers() == Qt::NoModifier);
1953 EditTrigger trigger = (selectedClicked ? SelectedClicked : NoEditTriggers);
1954 const bool edited = click && !d->pressClosedEditor ? edit(index, trigger, event) : false;
1955
1956 d->ctrlDragSelectionFlag = QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
1957
1958 if (d->selectionModel && d->noSelectionOnMousePress) {
1959 d->noSelectionOnMousePress = false;
1960 if (!d->pressClosedEditor)
1961 d->selectionModel->select(index, command: selectionCommand(index, event));
1962 }
1963
1964 d->pressClosedEditor = false;
1965 setState(NoState);
1966
1967 if (click) {
1968 if (event->button() == Qt::LeftButton)
1969 emit clicked(index);
1970 if (edited)
1971 return;
1972 QStyleOptionViewItem option;
1973 initViewItemOption(option: &option);
1974 if (d->pressedAlreadySelected)
1975 option.state |= QStyle::State_Selected;
1976 if ((d->model->flags(index) & Qt::ItemIsEnabled)
1977 && style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_ActivateItemOnSingleClick, opt: &option, widget: this))
1978 emit activated(index);
1979 }
1980}
1981
1982/*!
1983 This function is called with the given \a event when a mouse button is
1984 double clicked inside the widget. If the double-click is on a valid item it
1985 emits the doubleClicked() signal and calls edit() on the item.
1986*/
1987void QAbstractItemView::mouseDoubleClickEvent(QMouseEvent *event)
1988{
1989 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
1990
1991 QModelIndex index = indexAt(point: event->position().toPoint());
1992 if (!index.isValid()
1993 || !d->isIndexEnabled(index)
1994 || (d->pressedIndex != index)) {
1995 QMouseEvent me(QEvent::MouseButtonPress,
1996 event->position(), event->scenePosition(), event->globalPosition(),
1997 event->button(), event->buttons(), event->modifiers(),
1998 event->source(), event->pointingDevice());
1999 mousePressEvent(event: &me);
2000 return;
2001 }
2002 // signal handlers may change the model
2003 QPersistentModelIndex persistent = index;
2004 emit doubleClicked(index: persistent);
2005 if ((event->button() == Qt::LeftButton) && !edit(index: persistent, trigger: DoubleClicked, event)
2006 && !style()->styleHint(stylehint: QStyle::SH_ItemView_ActivateItemOnSingleClick, opt: nullptr, widget: this))
2007 emit activated(index: persistent);
2008 d->releaseFromDoubleClick = true;
2009}

2011#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
2012
2013/*!
2014 This function is called with the given \a event when a drag and drop operation enters
2015 the widget. If the drag is over a valid dropping place (e.g. over an item that
2016 accepts drops), the event is accepted; otherwise it is ignored.
2017
2018 \sa dropEvent(), startDrag()
2019*/
2020void QAbstractItemView::dragEnterEvent(QDragEnterEvent *event)
2021{
2022 if (dragDropMode() == InternalMove
2023 && (event->source() != this|| !(event->possibleActions() & Qt::MoveAction)))
2024 return;
2025
2026 if (d_func()->canDrop(event)) {
2027 event->accept();
2028 setState(DraggingState);
2029 } else {
2030 event->ignore();
2031 }
2032}
2033
2034/*!
2035 This function is called continuously with the given \a event during a drag and
2036 drop operation over the widget. It can cause the view to scroll if, for example,
2037 the user drags a selection to view's right or bottom edge. In this case, the
2038 event will be accepted; otherwise it will be ignored.
2039
2040 \sa dropEvent(), startDrag()
2041*/
2042void QAbstractItemView::dragMoveEvent(QDragMoveEvent *event)
2043{
2044 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
2045 d->draggedPosition = event->position().toPoint() + d->offset();
2046 if (dragDropMode() == InternalMove
2047 && (event->source() != this || !(event->possibleActions() & Qt::MoveAction)))
2048 return;
2049
2050 // ignore by default
2051 event->ignore();

2066 } else {
2067 d->dropIndicatorRect = QRect();

2069 break;
2070 case BelowItem:

2098 }

2101 } // can drop

2181/*!
2182 If the event hasn't already been accepted, determines the index to drop on.
2183
2184 if (row == -1 && col == -1)
2185 // append to this drop index
2186 else
2187 // place at row, col in drop index
2188
2189 If it returns \c true a drop can be done, and dropRow, dropCol and dropIndex reflects the position of the drop.
2190 \internal
2191 */
2192bool QAbstractItemViewPrivate::dropOn(QDropEvent *event, int *dropRow, int *dropCol, QModelIndex *dropIndex)
2193{
2194 Q_Q(QAbstractItemView);
2195 if (event->isAccepted())
2196 return false;
2197
2198 QModelIndex index;
2199 // rootIndex() (i.e. the viewport) might be a valid index
2200 if (viewport->rect().contains(p: event->position().toPoint())) {
2201 index = q->indexAt(point: event->position().toPoint());
2202 if (!index.isValid() || !q->visualRect(index).contains(p: event->position().toPoint()))
2203 index = root;
2204 }
2205
2206 // If we are allowed to do the drop
2207 if (model->supportedDropActions() & event->dropAction()) {
2208 int row = -1;
2209 int col = -1;
2210 if (index != root) {
2211 dropIndicatorPosition = position(pos: event->position().toPoint(), rect: q->visualRect(index), idx: index);
2212 switch (dropIndicatorPosition) {
2213 case QAbstractItemView::AboveItem:
2214 row = index.row();
2215 col = index.column();
2216 index = index.parent();
2217 break;
2218 case QAbstractItemView::BelowItem:
2219 row = index.row() + 1;
2220 col = index.column();
2221 index = index.parent();
2222 break;
2223 case QAbstractItemView::OnItem:
2224 case QAbstractItemView::OnViewport:
2225 break;
2226 }
2227 } else {
2228 dropIndicatorPosition = QAbstractItemView::OnViewport;
2229 }
2230 *dropIndex = index;
2231 *dropRow = row;
2232 *dropCol = col;
2233 if (!droppingOnItself(event, index))
2234 return true;
2235 }
2236 return false;
2237}

2239QAbstractItemView::DropIndicatorPosition
2240QAbstractItemViewPrivate::position(const QPoint &pos, const QRect &rect, const QModelIndex &index) const
2241{
2242 QAbstractItemView::DropIndicatorPosition r = QAbstractItemView::OnViewport;
2243 if (!overwrite) {
2244 const int margin = qBound(min: 2, val: qRound(d: qreal(rect.height()) / 5.5), max: 12);
2245 if (pos.y() - rect.top() < margin) {
2246 r = QAbstractItemView::AboveItem;

2248 r = QAbstractItemView::BelowItem;

2251 }
2252 } else {
2253 QRect touchingRect = rect;
2254 touchingRect.adjust(dx1: -1, dy1: -1, dx2: 1, dy2: 1);
2255 if (touchingRect.contains(p: pos, proper: false)) {
2256 r = QAbstractItemView::OnItem;
2257 }
2258 }
2259
2260 if (r == QAbstractItemView::OnItem && (!(model->flags(index) & Qt::ItemIsDropEnabled)))
2261 r = pos.y() < rect.center().y() ? QAbstractItemView::AboveItem : QAbstractItemView::BelowItem;

2634 if (delegate)
2635 delegate->setEditorData(editor: currentEditor, index: currentIndex());
2636 d->selectAllInEditor(w: currentEditor);

2639 currentEditor->setFocus();
2640 } else {
2641 // more pre-editing
2642 QApplication::sendEvent(receiver: currentEditor, event);
2643 }
2644 return;
2645 }
2646 } else if (preediting) {
2647 // don't set focus when the editor opens
2648 d->waitForIMCommit = true;
2649 // but pass preedit on to editor
2650 forwardEventToEditor = true;
2651 } else if (!commit) {

2654 }

2716}
2717
2718/*!
2719 Starts editing the item at \a index, creating an editor if
2720 necessary, and returns \c true if the view's \l{State} is now
2721 EditingState; otherwise returns \c false.
2722
2723 The action that caused the editing process is described by
2724 \a trigger, and the associated event is specified by \a event.
2725
2726 Editing can be forced by specifying the \a trigger to be
2727 QAbstractItemView::AllEditTriggers.
2728
2729 \sa closeEditor()
2730*/
2731bool QAbstractItemView::edit(const QModelIndex &index, EditTrigger trigger, QEvent *event)
2732{
2733 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
2734
2735 if (!d->isIndexValid(index))
2736 return false;
2737
2738 if (QWidget *w = (d->persistent.isEmpty() ? static_cast<QWidget*>(nullptr) : d->editorForIndex(index).widget.data())) {
2739 if (w->focusPolicy() == Qt::NoFocus)
2740 return false;
2741 if (!d->waitForIMCommit)
2742 w->setFocus();
2743 else
2744 updateMicroFocus();
2745 return true;
2746 }
2747
2748 if (trigger == DoubleClicked) {
2749 d->delayedEditing.stop();
2750 d->delayedAutoScroll.stop();
2751 } else if (trigger == CurrentChanged) {
2752 d->delayedEditing.stop();
2753 }
2754
2755 // in case e.g. setData() triggers a reset()
2756 QPersistentModelIndex safeIndex(index);
2757
2758 if (d->sendDelegateEvent(index, event)) {
2759 update(index: safeIndex);
2760 return true;
2761 }
2762
2763 if (!safeIndex.isValid()) {
2764 return false;
2765 }
2766
2767 // save the previous trigger before updating
2768 EditTriggers lastTrigger = d->lastTrigger;
2769 d->lastTrigger = trigger;
2770
2771 if (!d->shouldEdit(trigger, index: d->model->buddy(index: safeIndex)))
2772 return false;
2773
2774 if (d->delayedEditing.isActive())
2775 return false;
2776
2777 // we will receive a mouseButtonReleaseEvent after a
2778 // mouseDoubleClickEvent, so we need to check the previous trigger
2779 if (lastTrigger == DoubleClicked && trigger == SelectedClicked)
2780 return false;
2781
2782 // we may get a double click event later
2783 if (trigger == SelectedClicked)
2784 d->delayedEditing.start(msec: QApplication::doubleClickInterval(), obj: this);
2785 else
2786 d->openEditor(index: safeIndex, event: d->shouldForwardEvent(trigger, event) ? event : nullptr);
2787
2788 return true;
2789}

2801/*!
2802 \internal
2803 Updates the geometry of the open editor widgets in the view.
2804*/
2805void QAbstractItemView::updateEditorGeometries()
2806{
2807 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
2808 if (d->editorIndexHash.isEmpty())
2809 return;
2810 if (d->delayedPendingLayout) {
2811 // doItemsLayout() will end up calling this function again
2812 d->executePostedLayout();
2813 return;
2814 }
2815 QStyleOptionViewItem option;
2816 initViewItemOption(option: &option);
2817 QEditorIndexHash::iterator it = d->editorIndexHash.begin();
2818 QWidgetList editorsToRelease;
2819 QWidgetList editorsToHide;
2820 while (it != d->editorIndexHash.end()) {
2821 QModelIndex index = it.value();
2822 QWidget *editor = it.key();
2823 if (index.isValid() && editor) {
2824 option.rect = visualRect(index);
2825 if (option.rect.isValid()) {
2826 editor->show();
2827 QAbstractItemDelegate *delegate = itemDelegateForIndex(index);
2828 if (delegate)
2829 delegate->updateEditorGeometry(editor, option, index);
2830 } else {
2831 editorsToHide << editor;
2832 }
2833 ++it;
2834 } else {
2835 d->indexEditorHash.remove(key: it.value());
2836 it = d->editorIndexHash.erase(it);
2837 editorsToRelease << editor;
2838 }
2839 }
2840
2841 //we hide and release the editor outside of the loop because it might change the focus and try
2842 //to change the editors hashes.
2843 for (int i = 0; i < editorsToHide.size(); ++i) {
2844 editorsToHide.at(i)->hide();
2845 }
2846 for (int i = 0; i < editorsToRelease.size(); ++i) {
2847 d->releaseEditor(editor: editorsToRelease.at(i));
2848 }
2849}

2906/*!
2907 Closes the given \a editor, and releases it. The \a hint is
2908 used to specify how the view should respond to the end of the editing
2909 operation. For example, the hint may indicate that the next item in
2910 the view should be opened for editing.
2911
2912 \sa edit(), commitData()
2913*/
2914
2915void QAbstractItemView::closeEditor(QWidget *editor, QAbstractItemDelegate::EndEditHint hint)
2916{
2917 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
2918
2919 // Close the editor
2920 if (editor) {
2921 bool isPersistent = d->persistent.contains(value: editor);
2922 bool hadFocus = editor->hasFocus();
2923 QModelIndex index = d->indexForEditor(editor);
2924 if (!index.isValid()) {
2925 qWarning(msg: "QAbstractItemView::closeEditor called with an editor that does not belong to this view");
2926 return; // the editor was not registered
2927 }
2928
2929 // start a timer that expires immediately when we return to the event loop
2930 // to identify whether this close was triggered by a mousepress-initiated
2931 // focus event
2932 d->pressClosedEditorWatcher.start(msec: 0, obj: this);
2933 d->lastEditedIndex = index;
2934
2935 if (!isPersistent) {
2936 setState(NoState);
2937 QModelIndex index = d->indexForEditor(editor);
2938 editor->removeEventFilter(obj: itemDelegateForIndex(index));
2939 d->removeEditor(editor);
2940 }
2941 if (hadFocus) {
2942 if (focusPolicy() != Qt::NoFocus)
2943 setFocus(); // this will send a focusLost event to the editor
2944 else
2945 editor->clearFocus();
2946 } else {
2947 d->checkPersistentEditorFocus();
2948 }
2949
2950 QPointer<QWidget> ed = editor;
2951 QCoreApplication::sendPostedEvents(receiver: editor, event_type: 0);
2952 editor = ed;
2953
2954 if (!isPersistent && editor)
2955 d->releaseEditor(editor, index);
2956 }
2957
2958 // The EndEditHint part
2959 QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags flags = QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
2960 if (d->selectionMode != NoSelection)
2961 flags = QItemSelectionModel::ClearAndSelect | d->selectionBehaviorFlags();
2962 switch (hint) {
2963 case QAbstractItemDelegate::EditNextItem: {
2964 QModelIndex index = moveCursor(cursorAction: MoveNext, modifiers: Qt::NoModifier);
2965 if (index.isValid()) {
2966 QPersistentModelIndex persistent(index);
2967 d->selectionModel->setCurrentIndex(index: persistent, command: flags);
2968 // currentChanged signal would have already started editing
2969 if (index.flags() & Qt::ItemIsEditable
2970 && (!(editTriggers() & QAbstractItemView::CurrentChanged)))
2971 edit(index: persistent);
2972 } break; }
2973 case QAbstractItemDelegate::EditPreviousItem: {
2974 QModelIndex index = moveCursor(cursorAction: MovePrevious, modifiers: Qt::NoModifier);
2975 if (index.isValid()) {
2976 QPersistentModelIndex persistent(index);
2977 d->selectionModel->setCurrentIndex(index: persistent, command: flags);
2978 // currentChanged signal would have already started editing
2979 if (index.flags() & Qt::ItemIsEditable
2980 && (!(editTriggers() & QAbstractItemView::CurrentChanged)))
2981 edit(index: persistent);
2982 } break; }
2983 case QAbstractItemDelegate::SubmitModelCache:
2984 d->model->submit();
2985 break;
2986 case QAbstractItemDelegate::RevertModelCache:
2987 d->model->revert();
2988 break;
2989 default:
2990 break;
2991 }
2992}

3034/*!
3035 Moves to and selects the item best matching the string \a search.
3036 If no item is found nothing happens.
3037
3038 In the default implementation, the search is reset if \a search is empty, or
3039 the time interval since the last search has exceeded
3040 QApplication::keyboardInputInterval().
3041*/
3042void QAbstractItemView::keyboardSearch(const QString &search)
3043{
3044 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
3045 if (!d->model->rowCount(parent: d->root) || !d->model->columnCount(parent: d->root))
3046 return;
3047
3048 QModelIndex start = currentIndex().isValid() ? currentIndex()
3049 : d->model->index(row: 0, column: 0, parent: d->root);
3050 bool skipRow = false;
3051 bool keyboardTimeWasValid = d->keyboardInputTime.isValid();
3052 qint64 keyboardInputTimeElapsed;
3053 if (keyboardTimeWasValid)
3054 keyboardInputTimeElapsed = d->keyboardInputTime.restart();
3055 else
3056 d->keyboardInputTime.start();
3057 if (search.isEmpty() || !keyboardTimeWasValid
3058 || keyboardInputTimeElapsed > QApplication::keyboardInputInterval()) {
3059 d->keyboardInput = search;
3060 skipRow = currentIndex().isValid(); //if it is not valid we should really start at QModelIndex(0,0)
3061 } else {
3062 d->keyboardInput += search;
3063 }
3064
3065 // special case for searches with same key like 'aaaaa'
3066 bool sameKey = false;
3067 if (d->keyboardInput.size() > 1) {
3068 int c = d->keyboardInput.count(c: d->keyboardInput.at(i: d->keyboardInput.size() - 1));
3069 sameKey = (c == d->keyboardInput.size());
3070 if (sameKey)
3071 skipRow = true;
3072 }
3073
3074 // skip if we are searching for the same key or a new search started
3075 if (skipRow) {
3076 QModelIndex parent = start.parent();
3077 int newRow = (start.row() < d->model->rowCount(parent) - 1) ? start.row() + 1 : 0;
3078 start = d->model->index(row: newRow, column: start.column(), parent);
3079 }
3080
3081 // search from start with wraparound
3082 QModelIndex current = start;
3083 QModelIndexList match;
3084 QModelIndex firstMatch;
3085 QModelIndex startMatch;
3086 QModelIndexList previous;
3087 do {
3088 match = d->model->match(start: current, role: Qt::DisplayRole, value: d->keyboardInput);
3089 if (match == previous)
3090 break;
3091 firstMatch = match.value(i: 0);
3092 previous = match;
3093 if (firstMatch.isValid()) {
3094 if (d->isIndexEnabled(index: firstMatch)) {
3095 setCurrentIndex(firstMatch);
3096 break;
3097 }
3098 int row = firstMatch.row() + 1;
3099 if (row >= d->model->rowCount(parent: firstMatch.parent()))
3100 row = 0;
3101 current = firstMatch.sibling(arow: row, acolumn: firstMatch.column());
3102
3103 //avoid infinite loop if all the matching items are disabled.
3104 if (!startMatch.isValid())
3105 startMatch = firstMatch;
3106 else if (startMatch == firstMatch)
3107 break;
3108 }
3109 } while (current != start && firstMatch.isValid());
3110}

3366/*!
3367 This slot is called when items with the given \a roles are changed in the
3368 model. The changed items are those from \a topLeft to \a bottomRight
3369 inclusive. If just one item is changed \a topLeft == \a bottomRight.
3370
3371 The \a roles which have been changed can either be an empty container (meaning everything
3372 has changed), or a non-empty container with the subset of roles which have changed.
3373
3374 \note: Qt::ToolTipRole is not honored by dataChanged() in the views provided by Qt.
3375*/
3376void QAbstractItemView::dataChanged(const QModelIndex &topLeft, const QModelIndex &bottomRight,
3377 const QList<int> &roles)
3378{
3379 Q_UNUSED(roles);
3380 // Single item changed
3381 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
3382 if (topLeft == bottomRight && topLeft.isValid()) {
3383 const QEditorInfo &editorInfo = d->editorForIndex(index: topLeft);
3384 //we don't update the edit data if it is static
3385 if (!editorInfo.isStatic && editorInfo.widget) {
3386 QAbstractItemDelegate *delegate = itemDelegateForIndex(index: topLeft);
3387 if (delegate) {
3388 delegate->setEditorData(editor: editorInfo.widget.data(), index: topLeft);
3389 }
3390 }
3391 if (isVisible() && !d->delayedPendingLayout) {
3392 // otherwise the items will be update later anyway
3393 update(index: topLeft);
3394 }
3395 } else {
3396 d->updateEditorData(topLeft, bottomRight);
3397 if (isVisible() && !d->delayedPendingLayout) {
3398 if (!topLeft.isValid() ||
3399 topLeft.parent() != bottomRight.parent() ||
3400 topLeft.row() > bottomRight.row() ||
3401 topLeft.column() > bottomRight.column()) {
3402 // invalid parameter - call update() to redraw all
3403 d->viewport->update();
3404 } else {
3405 const QRect updateRect = d->intersectedRect(rect: d->viewport->rect(), topLeft, bottomRight);

3441/*!
3442 This slot is called when rows are about to be removed. The deleted rows are
3443 those under the given \a parent from \a start to \a end inclusive.
3444
3445 \sa rowsInserted()
3446*/
3447void QAbstractItemView::rowsAboutToBeRemoved(const QModelIndex &parent, int start, int end)
3448{
3449 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
3450
3451 setState(CollapsingState);
3452
3453 // Ensure one selected item in single selection mode.
3454 QModelIndex current = currentIndex();
3455 if (d->selectionMode == SingleSelection
3456 && current.isValid()
3457 && current.row() >= start
3458 && current.row() <= end
3459 && current.parent() == parent) {
3460 int totalToRemove = end - start + 1;
3461 if (d->model->rowCount(parent) <= totalToRemove) { // no more children
3462 QModelIndex index = parent;
3463 while (index != d->root && !d->isIndexEnabled(index))
3464 index = index.parent();
3465 if (index != d->root)
3466 setCurrentIndex(index);
3467 } else {
3468 int row = end + 1;
3469 QModelIndex next;
3470 const int rowCount = d->model->rowCount(parent);
3471 bool found = false;
3472 // find the next visible and enabled item
3473 while (row < rowCount && !found) {
3474 next = d->model->index(row: row++, column: current.column(), parent: current.parent());
3475#ifdef QT_DEBUG
3476 if (!next.isValid()) {
3477 qWarning("Model unexpectedly returned an invalid index");
3478 break;
3479 }
3480#endif
3481 if (!isIndexHidden(index: next) && d->isIndexEnabled(index: next)) {
3482 found = true;
3483 break;
3484 }
3485 }
3486
3487 if (!found) {
3488 row = start - 1;
3489 // find the previous visible and enabled item
3490 while (row >= 0) {
3491 next = d->model->index(row: row--, column: current.column(), parent: current.parent());
3492#ifdef QT_DEBUG
3493 if (!next.isValid()) {
3494 qWarning("Model unexpectedly returned an invalid index");
3495 break;
3496 }
3497#endif
3498 if (!isIndexHidden(index: next) && d->isIndexEnabled(index: next))
3499 break;
3500 }
3501 }
3502
3503 setCurrentIndex(next);
3504 }
3505 }
3506
3507 // Remove all affected editors; this is more efficient than waiting for updateGeometries() to clean out editors for invalid indexes
3508 QEditorIndexHash::iterator i = d->editorIndexHash.begin();
3509 while (i != d->editorIndexHash.end()) {
3510 const QModelIndex index = i.value();
3511 if (index.row() >= start && index.row() <= end && d->model->parent(child: index) == parent) {
3512 QWidget *editor = i.key();
3513 QEditorInfo info = d->indexEditorHash.take(key: index);
3514 i = d->editorIndexHash.erase(it: i);
3515 if (info.widget)
3516 d->releaseEditor(editor, index);
3517 } else {
3518 ++i;
3519 }
3520 }
3521}

3756/*!
3757 This slot is called when a new item becomes the current item.
3758 The previous current item is specified by the \a previous index, and the new
3759 item by the \a current index.
3760
3761 If you want to know about changes to items see the
3762 dataChanged() signal.
3763*/
3764void QAbstractItemView::currentChanged(const QModelIndex &current, const QModelIndex &previous)
3765{
3766 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
3767 Q_ASSERT(d->model);
3768
3769 if (previous.isValid()) {
3770 QModelIndex buddy = d->model->buddy(index: previous);
3771 QWidget *editor = d->editorForIndex(index: buddy).widget.data();
3772 if (editor && !d->persistent.contains(value: editor)) {
3773 commitData(editor);
3774 if (current.row() != previous.row())
3775 closeEditor(editor, hint: QAbstractItemDelegate::SubmitModelCache);
3776 else
3777 closeEditor(editor, hint: QAbstractItemDelegate::NoHint);
3778 }
3779 if (isVisible()) {
3780 update(index: previous);
3781 }
3782 }
3783
3784 if (current.isValid() && !d->autoScrollTimer.isActive()) {
3785 if (isVisible()) {
3786 if (d->autoScroll)
3787 scrollTo(index: current);
3788 update(index: current);
3789 edit(index: current, trigger: CurrentChanged, event: nullptr);
3790 if (current.row() == (d->model->rowCount(parent: d->root) - 1))
3791 d->fetchMore();
3792 } else {
3793 d->shouldScrollToCurrentOnShow = d->autoScroll;
3794 }
3795 }

3803void QAbstractItemView::startDrag(Qt::DropActions supportedActions)

3991
3992/*!
3993 \internal
3994*/
3995void QAbstractItemView::doAutoScroll()
3996{
3997 // find how much we should scroll with
3998 Q_D(QAbstractItemView);
3999 QScrollBar *verticalScroll = verticalScrollBar();
4000 QScrollBar *horizontalScroll = horizontalScrollBar();
4001
4002 // QHeaderView does not (normally) have scrollbars
4003 // It needs to use its parents scroll instead
4004 QHeaderView *hv = qobject_cast<QHeaderView*>(object: this);
4005 if (hv) {
4006 QAbstractScrollArea *parent = qobject_cast<QAbstractScrollArea*>(object: parentWidget());
4007 if (parent) {
4008 if (hv->orientation() == Qt::Horizontal) {
4009 if (!hv->horizontalScrollBar() || !hv->horizontalScrollBar()->isVisible())
4010 horizontalScroll = parent->horizontalScrollBar();
4011 } else {
4012 if (!hv->verticalScrollBar() || !hv->verticalScrollBar()->isVisible())
4013 verticalScroll = parent->verticalScrollBar();
4014 }
4015 }
4016 }
4017
4018 const int verticalStep = verticalScroll->pageStep();
4019 const int horizontalStep = horizontalScroll->pageStep();
4020 if (d->autoScrollCount < qMax(a: verticalStep, b: horizontalStep))
4021 ++d->autoScrollCount;
4022
4023 const int margin = d->autoScrollMargin;
4024 const int verticalValue = verticalScroll->value();
4025 const int horizontalValue = horizontalScroll->value();
4026
4027 const QPoint pos = d->draggedPosition - d->offset();
4028 const QRect area = QWidgetPrivate::get(w: d->viewport)->clipRect();
4029
4030 // do the scrolling if we are in the scroll margins
4031 if (pos.y() - area.top() < margin)
4032 verticalScroll->setValue(verticalValue - d->autoScrollCount);
4033 else if (area.bottom() - pos.y() < margin)
4034 verticalScroll->setValue(verticalValue + d->autoScrollCount);
4035 if (pos.x() - area.left() < margin)
4036 horizontalScroll->setValue(horizontalValue - d->autoScrollCount);
4037 else if (area.right() - pos.x() < margin)
4038 horizontalScroll->setValue(horizontalValue + d->autoScrollCount);
4039 // if nothing changed, stop scrolling
4040 const bool verticalUnchanged = (verticalValue == verticalScroll->value());
4041 const bool horizontalUnchanged = (horizontalValue == horizontalScroll->value());
4042 if (verticalUnchanged && horizontalUnchanged) {
4043 stopAutoScroll();
4044 } else {
4045#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
4046 d->dropIndicatorRect = QRect();
4047 d->dropIndicatorPosition = QAbstractItemView::OnViewport;
4048#endif
4049 switch (state()) {
4050 case QAbstractItemView::DragSelectingState: {
4051 // mouseMoveEvent updates the drag-selection rectangle, so fake an event. This also
4052 // updates draggedPosition taking the now scrolled viewport into account.
4053 const QPoint globalPos = d->viewport->mapToGlobal(pos);
4054 const QPoint windowPos = window()->mapFromGlobal(globalPos);
4055 QMouseEvent mm(QEvent::MouseMove, pos, windowPos, globalPos,
4056 Qt::NoButton, Qt::LeftButton, d->pressedModifiers,
4057 Qt::MouseEventSynthesizedByQt);
4058 QApplication::sendEvent(receiver: viewport(), event: &mm);
4059 break;
4060 }
4061 case QAbstractItemView::DraggingState: {
4062 // we can't simulate mouse (it would throw off the drag'n'drop state logic) or drag
4063 // (we don't have the mime data or the actions) move events during drag'n'drop, so
4064 // update our dragged position manually after the scroll. "pos" is the old
4065 // draggedPosition - d->offset(), and d->offset() is now updated after scrolling, so
4066 // pos + d->offset() gives us the new position.
4067 d->draggedPosition = pos + d->offset();
4068 break;
4069 }
4070 default:
4071 break;
4072 }
4073 d->viewport->update();
4074 }
4075}
4076
4077/*!
4078 Returns the SelectionFlags to be used when updating a selection model
4079 for the specified \a index. The result depends on the current
4080 selectionMode(), and on the user input event \a event, which can be
4081 \nullptr.
4082
4083 Reimplement this function to define your own selection behavior.
4084
4085 \sa setSelection()
4086*/
4087QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags QAbstractItemView::selectionCommand(const QModelIndex &index,
4088 const QEvent *event) const
4089{
4090 Q_D(const QAbstractItemView);
4091 Qt::KeyboardModifiers keyModifiers = event && event->isInputEvent()
4092 ? static_cast<const QInputEvent*>(event)->modifiers()
4093 : Qt::NoModifier;
4094 switch (d->selectionMode) {
4095 case NoSelection: // Never update selection model
4096 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4097 case SingleSelection: // ClearAndSelect on valid index otherwise NoUpdate
4098 if (event) {
4099 switch (event->type()) {
4100 case QEvent::MouseButtonPress:
4101 // press with any modifiers on a selected item does nothing
4102 if (d->pressedAlreadySelected)
4103 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4104 break;
4105 case QEvent::MouseButtonRelease:
4106 // clicking into area with no items does nothing
4107 if (!index.isValid())
4108 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4109 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
4110 case QEvent::KeyPress:
4111 // ctrl-release on selected item deselects
4112 if ((keyModifiers & Qt::ControlModifier) && d->selectionModel->isSelected(index))
4113 return QItemSelectionModel::Deselect | d->selectionBehaviorFlags();
4114 break;
4115 default:
4116 break;
4117 }
4118 }
4119 return QItemSelectionModel::ClearAndSelect | d->selectionBehaviorFlags();
4120 case MultiSelection:
4121 return d->multiSelectionCommand(index, event);
4122 case ExtendedSelection:
4123 return d->extendedSelectionCommand(index, event);
4124 case ContiguousSelection:
4125 return d->contiguousSelectionCommand(index, event);
4126 }
4127 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4128}
4129
4130QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags QAbstractItemViewPrivate::multiSelectionCommand(
4131 const QModelIndex &index, const QEvent *event) const
4132{
4133 Q_UNUSED(index);
4134
4135 if (event) {
4136 switch (event->type()) {
4137 case QEvent::KeyPress:
4138 if (static_cast<const QKeyEvent*>(event)->key() == Qt::Key_Space
4139 || static_cast<const QKeyEvent*>(event)->key() == Qt::Key_Select)
4140 return QItemSelectionModel::Toggle|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4141 break;
4142 case QEvent::MouseButtonPress:
4143 if (static_cast<const QMouseEvent*>(event)->button() == Qt::LeftButton) {
4144 // since the press might start a drag, deselect only on release
4145 if (!pressedAlreadySelected
4146#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
4147 || !dragEnabled || !isIndexDragEnabled(index)
4148#endif
4149 )
4150 return QItemSelectionModel::Toggle|selectionBehaviorFlags(); // toggle
4151 }
4152 break;
4153 case QEvent::MouseButtonRelease:
4154 if (static_cast<const QMouseEvent*>(event)->button() == Qt::LeftButton) {
4155 if (pressedAlreadySelected
4156#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
4157 && dragEnabled && isIndexDragEnabled(index)
4158#endif
4159 && index == pressedIndex)
4160 return QItemSelectionModel::Toggle|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4161 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate|selectionBehaviorFlags(); // finalize
4162 }
4163 break;
4164 case QEvent::MouseMove:
4165 if (static_cast<const QMouseEvent*>(event)->buttons() & Qt::LeftButton)
4166 return QItemSelectionModel::ToggleCurrent|selectionBehaviorFlags(); // toggle drag select
4167 break;
4168 default:
4169 break;
4170 }
4171 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4172 }
4173
4174 return QItemSelectionModel::Toggle|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4175}
4176
4177QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags QAbstractItemViewPrivate::extendedSelectionCommand(
4178 const QModelIndex &index, const QEvent *event) const
4179{
4180 Qt::KeyboardModifiers modifiers = event && event->isInputEvent()
4181 ? static_cast<const QInputEvent*>(event)->modifiers()
4182 : QGuiApplication::keyboardModifiers();
4183 if (event) {
4184 switch (event->type()) {
4185 case QEvent::MouseMove: {
4186 // Toggle on MouseMove
4187 if (modifiers & Qt::ControlModifier)
4188 return QItemSelectionModel::ToggleCurrent|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4189 break;
4190 }
4191 case QEvent::MouseButtonPress: {
4192 const Qt::MouseButton button = static_cast<const QMouseEvent*>(event)->button();
4193 const bool rightButtonPressed = button & Qt::RightButton;
4194 const bool shiftKeyPressed = modifiers & Qt::ShiftModifier;
4195 const bool controlKeyPressed = modifiers & Qt::ControlModifier;
4196 const bool indexIsSelected = selectionModel->isSelected(index);
4197 if ((shiftKeyPressed || controlKeyPressed) && rightButtonPressed)
4198 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4199 if (!shiftKeyPressed && !controlKeyPressed && indexIsSelected)
4200 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4201 if (!index.isValid() && !rightButtonPressed && !shiftKeyPressed && !controlKeyPressed)
4202 return QItemSelectionModel::Clear;
4203 if (!index.isValid())
4204 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4205 // since the press might start a drag, deselect only on release
4206 if (controlKeyPressed && !rightButtonPressed && pressedAlreadySelected
4207#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
4208 && dragEnabled && isIndexDragEnabled(index)
4209#endif
4210 ) {
4211 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4212 }
4213 break;
4214 }
4215 case QEvent::MouseButtonRelease: {
4216 // ClearAndSelect on MouseButtonRelease if MouseButtonPress on selected item or empty area
4217 const Qt::MouseButton button = static_cast<const QMouseEvent*>(event)->button();
4218 const bool rightButtonPressed = button & Qt::RightButton;
4219 const bool shiftKeyPressed = modifiers & Qt::ShiftModifier;
4220 const bool controlKeyPressed = modifiers & Qt::ControlModifier;
4221 if (((index == pressedIndex && selectionModel->isSelected(index))
4222 || !index.isValid()) && state != QAbstractItemView::DragSelectingState
4223 && !shiftKeyPressed && !controlKeyPressed && (!rightButtonPressed || !index.isValid()))
4224 return QItemSelectionModel::ClearAndSelect|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4225 if (index == pressedIndex && controlKeyPressed && !rightButtonPressed
4226#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
4227 && dragEnabled && isIndexDragEnabled(index)
4228#endif
4229 ) {
4230 break;
4231 }
4232 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4233 }
4234 case QEvent::KeyPress: {
4235 // NoUpdate on Key movement and Ctrl
4236 switch (static_cast<const QKeyEvent*>(event)->key()) {
4237 case Qt::Key_Backtab:
4238 modifiers = modifiers & ~Qt::ShiftModifier; // special case for backtab
4239 Q_FALLTHROUGH();
4240 case Qt::Key_Down:
4241 case Qt::Key_Up:
4242 case Qt::Key_Left:
4243 case Qt::Key_Right:
4244 case Qt::Key_Home:
4245 case Qt::Key_End:
4246 case Qt::Key_PageUp:
4247 case Qt::Key_PageDown:
4248 case Qt::Key_Tab:
4249 if (modifiers & Qt::ControlModifier
4250#ifdef QT_KEYPAD_NAVIGATION
4251 // Preserve historical tab order navigation behavior
4252 || QApplication::navigationMode() == Qt::NavigationModeKeypadTabOrder
4253#endif
4254 )
4255 return QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate;
4256 break;
4257 case Qt::Key_Select:
4258 return QItemSelectionModel::Toggle|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4259 case Qt::Key_Space:// Toggle on Ctrl-Qt::Key_Space, Select on Space
4260 if (modifiers & Qt::ControlModifier)
4261 return QItemSelectionModel::Toggle|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4262 return QItemSelectionModel::Select|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4263 default:
4264 break;
4265 }
4266 }
4267 default:
4268 break;
4269 }
4270 }
4271
4272 if (modifiers & Qt::ShiftModifier)
4273 return QItemSelectionModel::SelectCurrent|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4274 if (modifiers & Qt::ControlModifier)
4275 return QItemSelectionModel::Toggle|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4276 if (state == QAbstractItemView::DragSelectingState) {
4277 //when drag-selecting we need to clear any previous selection and select the current one
4278 return QItemSelectionModel::Clear|QItemSelectionModel::SelectCurrent|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4279 }
4280
4281 return QItemSelectionModel::ClearAndSelect|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4282}
4283
4284QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags
4285QAbstractItemViewPrivate::contiguousSelectionCommand(const QModelIndex &index,
4286 const QEvent *event) const
4287{
4288 QItemSelectionModel::SelectionFlags flags = extendedSelectionCommand(index, event);
4289 const int Mask = QItemSelectionModel::Clear | QItemSelectionModel::Select
4290 | QItemSelectionModel::Deselect | QItemSelectionModel::Toggle
4291 | QItemSelectionModel::Current;
4292
4293 switch (flags & Mask) {
4294 case QItemSelectionModel::Clear:
4295 case QItemSelectionModel::ClearAndSelect:
4296 case QItemSelectionModel::SelectCurrent:
4297 return flags;
4298 case QItemSelectionModel::NoUpdate:
4299 if (event &&
4300 (event->type() == QEvent::MouseButtonPress
4301 || event->type() == QEvent::MouseButtonRelease))
4302 return flags;
4303 return QItemSelectionModel::ClearAndSelect|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4304 default:
4305 return QItemSelectionModel::SelectCurrent|selectionBehaviorFlags();
4306 }
4307}

4326bool QAbstractItemViewPrivate::shouldEdit(QAbstractItemView::EditTrigger trigger,
4327 const QModelIndex &index) const
4328{
4329 if (!index.isValid())
4330 return false;
4331 Qt::ItemFlags flags = model->flags(index);
4332 if (((flags & Qt::ItemIsEditable) == 0) || ((flags & Qt::ItemIsEnabled) == 0))
4333 return false;
4334 if (state == QAbstractItemView::EditingState)
4335 return false;
4336 if (hasEditor(index))
4337 return false;
4338 if (trigger == QAbstractItemView::AllEditTriggers) // force editing
4339 return true;
4340 if ((trigger & editTriggers) == QAbstractItemView::SelectedClicked
4341 && !selectionModel->isSelected(index))
4342 return false;
4343 return (trigger & editTriggers);
4344}

4448void QAbstractItemViewPrivate::updateEditorData(const QModelIndex &tl, const QModelIndex &br)
4449{
4450 Q_Q(QAbstractItemView);
4451 // we are counting on having relatively few editors
4452 const bool checkIndexes = tl.isValid() && br.isValid();
4453 const QModelIndex parent = tl.parent();
4454 // QTBUG-25370: We need to copy the indexEditorHash, because while we're
4455 // iterating over it, we are calling methods which can allow user code to
4456 // call a method on *this which can modify the member indexEditorHash.
4457 const QIndexEditorHash indexEditorHashCopy = indexEditorHash;
4458 QIndexEditorHash::const_iterator it = indexEditorHashCopy.constBegin();
4459 for (; it != indexEditorHashCopy.constEnd(); ++it) {
4460 QWidget *editor = it.value().widget.data();
4461 const QModelIndex index = it.key();
4462 if (it.value().isStatic || !editor || !index.isValid() ||
4463 (checkIndexes
4464 && (index.row() < tl.row() || index.row() > br.row()
4465 || index.column() < tl.column() || index.column() > br.column()
4466 || index.parent() != parent)))
4467 continue;
4468
4469 QAbstractItemDelegate *delegate = q->itemDelegateForIndex(index);
4470 if (delegate) {
4471 delegate->setEditorData(editor, index);
4472 }
4473 }

4476/*!
4477 \internal
4478
4479 In DND if something has been moved then this is called.
4480 Typically this means you should "remove" the selected item or row,
4481 but the behavior is view-dependent (table just clears the selected indexes for example).
4482
4483 Either remove the selected rows or clear them
4484*/
4485void QAbstractItemViewPrivate::clearOrRemove()
4486{
4487#if QT_CONFIG(draganddrop)
4488 const QItemSelection selection = selectionModel->selection();
4489 QList<QItemSelectionRange>::const_iterator it = selection.constBegin();
4490
4491 if (!overwrite) {
4492 for (; it != selection.constEnd(); ++it) {
4493 QModelIndex parent = (*it).parent();
4494 if ((*it).left() != 0)
4495 continue;
4496 if ((*it).right() != (model->columnCount(parent) - 1))
4497 continue;
4498 int count = (*it).bottom() - (*it).top() + 1;
4499 model->removeRows(row: (*it).top(), count, parent);
4500 }
4501 } else {
4502 // we can't remove the rows so reset the items (i.e. the view is like a table)
4503 QModelIndexList list = selection.indexes();
4504 for (int i=0; i < list.size(); ++i) {
4505 QModelIndex index = list.at(i);
4506 QMap<int, QVariant> roles = model->itemData(index);
4507 for (QMap<int, QVariant>::Iterator it = roles.begin(); it != roles.end(); ++it)
4508 it.value() = QVariant();
4509 model->setItemData(index, roles);
4510 }
4511 }
4512#endif
4513}
